Bezhanpour accused the West of not investigating the allegations of war crimes in Afghanistan and seeking to exaggerate such investigations to achieve other goals.&#160;

"It means that the West has always tried to exaggerate the issue instead of genuinely investigate the crimes. They had gone there [Afghanistan] to commit crimes. The soldiers [deployed there] were told that people would be killed, and they [the soldiers] would [also] be killed there. Whatever happened had been pledged and agreed," he said.&#160;

