Describing the UK inquiry into the war crimes allegation as "propaganda", Stanikzai said: "Anyway, it is propaganda."

"Crimes had been committed in Afghanistan. Not only the British but also Germans had martyred 97 children and injured hundreds of others in Kunduz Province. Nobody has so far been put on trial. Nobody has been held accountable for it," he added.&#160;

