"Under the pretext of fighting terrorism, they had invaded Afghanistan. They stayed in Afghanistan for 20 years and committed crimes that were not confined to only one to two individuals. Americans, claiming to fight terrorism, came to Afghanistan primarily to achieve their own goals," he said.

"One of the tactics Americans used at the&#160;Bonn Conference&#160;was to establish the Afghan National Army, police and security forces. Americans at the Bonn Conference established the three organisations to reduce its casualties on the battlefield," claimed Ahmadzai.&#160;

Concluding, he said that such inquiries could not hold accountable the leaders who had ordered the deployment of forces to Afghanistan, which resulted in the "war crimes".&#160;

