The situation around our country is growing worse. People are trying to drag us into processes which are completely detached from our own constructive interests. During a working visit to Hrodna Region, The [Belarusian] president [Alyaksandr Lukashenka, Alexander Lukashenko] stressed that any provocation against us would be cut off hard and fast.&#160;

[Insertion] Belarusian President Alyaksandr Lukashenka, during a meeting to assess the battle readiness of units and groups in Ashmyanski District on 26 March 2024: &#160;"If they violate the state border - destroy them. No-one should be handled with kid gloves. And that is how we will act. Because any violation of the state border means destruction. They only understand force."&#160;

Why one needs to know history

The West is trying to tie us up in an arms race, and push us to militarise fruitful border lands and get us to pour human and material resources into military programmes and events. Military contingents belonging to countries whose capital are thousands of kilometres from us and with whom we have no common borders are being deployed densely along our border. The goal in this is clear - they are testing our resilience.&#160;

German battalions and an American tank battalion have already taken up military positions in Lithuania's Pabrade. All of this is being done with clear designs of sabotage in mind.&#160;

Almost 150 Nato military, transport and reconnaissance aircraft are now based at Lithuanian airfields. The intensity and nature of this aviation group along our border is not merely hostile, they are provocative in every sense.&#160;

Thousands of Nato soldiers are training their battle skills at military training fields 15 kilometres from our border, working out tactics and ways of invading our territory.&#160;

Along the southern line, we already see the positions reflecting the best French lines dating to the era of Napoleon, whose standards are still remembered from the disgraceful rout in 1813 and the frozen fingers of French soldiers who miraculously survived Belarusian partisans, first on their way to Moscow and then on their way back to Paris.&#160;

And just like carbon copy paper, the gloomy and infamous Bundeswehr has decided to accommodate itself to our north. During the Great Patriotic War they also got it handed to them by republican partisans. So bad that steel German boot heels flashed as they ran away.&#160;

Is history for them really so covered in honey? One wonders why they are coming back again?

A convincing warning

Here I must note that any of our offers about transparent relations, peace initiatives and cooperation have been unilaterally rejected and flatly blocked with open hostility.

Unfortunately, we have been forced to mirror these actions on our side. But our main objective is not to frighten, but to convince the military leadership of our neighbours that we are not here hunting mushrooms, that we are not joking around and that any provocation will be cut off hard and fast without any warning shot or any chance for a second take. We have been patient for too long in indulging the disdain they have for us to even inadvertently push a peaceful situation into the rut of a conflict. But that was possible at former balances of force.

Now we see a systemic growth on the line of contact along our border. The growth of military potential enabled by the administrations of our neighbours makes any condescension not only improper, but also very dangerous for our country and population.

Those who accuse us of threatening to attack were the first to exit peace agreements and revoke and break all agreements about military parity. The bordering side treats any step towards agreement exclusively as a loss and defeat. And so there is no-one to make any agreement with on any topic today.&#160;

Yes, that line of behaviour was put in place by those who inhabit Nato's eastern flank. And by this same scheme, they are the kamikazes of the North Atlantic alliance. Well, what else can one think about countries where the last drops of industry and economy are being destroyed and whose territory is being used to move military infrastructure for Nato contingents towards Drang nach Osten? They are simply being used in the classic, throwaway scenario. And that's it. Nothing more.

That is what the president is trying to warn colleague neighbours in the Baltics, Poland and Ukraine.&#160;

A fragile edge

During an inspection of units and subunits along the border in Hrodna Region, the head of state took the moment to demonstrate that we are also serious, but that we have a better plan, which would allow everyone, and not just one side, to survive. We are calling on our neighbours to stop and not unloose the knot of aggression.

Everyone has already practically shown they are ready to and capable of crossing into what we call active movement. There is no sense in sabre rattling. Our side does not intend to war with our neighbours, the West, Nato or anyone at all - that is our main message to everyone. We are happy to turn our swords into plowshares, just give us a reason. For now it is impossible to get rid of the fear always threatening everyone.&#160;

Lukashenka noted in Hrodna Region that we are an economically and politically strong country, we are a nuclear and space state and the "red lines" are not just a drawing on a map, but the thin and fragile edge between life and death. We only want one thing - mutual respect. And so the president's peaceful message to our neighbours is like that marking on fragile cargo designating everyone's responsibility for peace and life - "do not shake and do not throw".

